    checks (2 sites), _discardingPonderBestmove lock unification (8 writes),
    URL scheme case-insensitivity (3 sites), HapticHelper removal, StatsActivity
    volatile + lifecycle, EngineConfigHelper retry + comments, StabilizationHelper
    hot-path, TlsSecurityHelper constant-time, FileIoHelper rename, PermissionHelper
    3000-range codes, BuildConfig.VERSION_NAME unification (3 sites), EngineService
    isRunning timing, build.gradle cleanup, AndroidManifest cleanup, proguard-rules
    comment fixes.
  - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): Extracted PROCESS_DESTROY_GRACE_MS = 100
    constant for the 2 remaining Thread.sleep(100) calls in
    cleanupEngineResources() and shutdown() (semantically distinct from
    PONDER_STOP_GRACE_MS). No Thread.sleep(100) magic numbers remain.
  - StatsActivity.java (AGPL v3): Removed redundant second Uri.parse(trimmed)
    call in openUrlInBrowser — the first parse is now reused for the Intent.
  - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): Corrected comment direction ("above"
    not "below" — start() is above applyTransform() in source order).
  - proguard-rules.pro (AGPL v3): Rewrote section-3 comment (same direction-
    inversion bug as the round-10 section-6 fix). Now consistent with section-6.
  - No new Java files. No license classification changes.

v1.2.1 round-10 (2026.7.14) — deep fix of review-D/E/F P2/P3 items:
  - HapticHelper.java (GPL v3): REMOVED ENTIRELY. The class was a Phase 73
    extraction that was instantiated in StockfishNative (_hapticHelper =
    new HapticHelper(...)) but never invoked. StockfishNative.performHaptic
    calls the inline performHapticInternal directly. Removed: the class
    file, the field declaration, and the instantiation. License
    classification: HapticHelper is no longer in the GPL v3 file list.
  - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): P2 concurrency hardening —
    _restartInProgress lock consistency (all 14 =false writes now go
    through _clearRestartInProgress() helper that takes _restartLock);
    recoverEngine shutdownRequested checks (startEngineInternal entry +
    after executor recreation); _discardingPonderBestmove lock unification
    (3 additional write sites wrapped in _discardFlagLock). P3 readability
    — magic numbers extracted (MIN_ENGINE_BINARY_SIZE, PONDER_STOP_GRACE_MS);
    escapeJsString dead-code simplification; isProcessAlive SDK_INT
    pre-check; _pendingChess960 field relocated; if(ctx==null) dead code
    removed; "remove JNI bridge" comment rewritten.
  - StatsActivity.java (AGPL v3): P2 — statsPayload is now volatile;
    added onPause/onResume overrides calling webView.onPause()/onResume().
  - EngineConfigHelper.java (GPL v3): P2 — detectBigCoreCount no longer
    caches failure results (allows retry on transient /proc/cpuinfo read
    failure); added mid-search context comments to setGameDifficulty and
    forceFullStrength.
  - StabilizationHelper.java (AGPL v3): P2 — applyTransform hot-path
    optimization (removeProperty('--stab-rot') moved from per-frame to
    one-time in start()).
  - TlsSecurityHelper.java (AGPL v3): P2 — validatePin now uses
    MessageDigest.isEqual on raw 32-byte SHA-256 digest against pre-decoded
    pin bytes (constant-time comparison).
  - ChessWebViewClient.java (AGPL v3): P2 — shouldOverrideUrlLoading now
    uses Uri.parse + equalsIgnoreCase for case-insensitive http(s) scheme
    check (RFC 3986 §3.1). P3 (continuation) — header doc-comment updated
    to note the round-10 URL scheme change.
  - No new Java files.

v1.2.1 round-10 continuation (2026.7.14) — secondary review-E items:
  - FileIoHelper.java (GPL v3): P2 — renamed ensureReadExternalStoragePermission
    → requestReadExternalStoragePermission (the previous "ensure" name implied
    a synchronous guarantee, but Activity.requestPermissions is asynchronous).
    Extracted hardcoded request code 1002 to named constant
    REQUEST_CODE_READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.
  - PermissionHelper.java (GPL v3): P2 — migrated hardcoded permission
    request codes from 1000-range (1001 storage / 1003 notification, which
    overlapped with SafPickerHelper's REQUEST_CODE_IMPORT_SETTINGS=1001 /
    REQUEST_CODE_IMPORT_PGN=1003) to disjoint 3000-range
    (REQUEST_CODE_STORAGE_PERMISSION=3001 /
    REQUEST_CODE_NOTIFICATION_PERMISSION=3002). No functional change —
    requestPermissions and startActivityForResult dispatch through different
    Activity callbacks, and MainActivity has no onRequestPermissionsResult
    handler; the overlap was confusing for maintenance only.
  - ChessApp.java (AGPL v3): P3 — replaced hardcoded "v1.2.1" in the init-log
    line with BuildConfig.VERSION_NAME (auto-generated by AGP from
    build.gradle's versionName).
  - MainActivity.java (AGPL v3): P3 — replaced private static final String
    VERSION = "v1.2.1" with "v" + BuildConfig.VERSION_NAME. This field drives
    the title display ("Regalia v1.2.1").
  - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3): P3 — replaced private static final String
    ENGINE_VERSION = "v1.2.1" with "v" + BuildConfig.VERSION_NAME. Despite
    the name "ENGINE_VERSION", this is the APP version exposed to JS via
    getEngineVersion() (the actual Stockfish engine version comes from the
    "uci" handshake's "id name" line, stored in engineName). Field name
    retained for API stability.
  - EngineService.java (AGPL v3): P3 — moved isRunning = true from the top
    of onCreate() (before createNotificationChannel / startForeground) to
    AFTER startForeground() succeeds. If startForeground throws (e.g.
    ForegroundServiceTypeNotAllowed on Android 14+ if the FGS subtype
    property were ever missing), isRunning is no longer left true while
    the service is actually dead.
  - No new Java files. No license classification changes.
