  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev30 changes:
    - ChessWebViewClient.java (AGPL v3): ROBUSTNESS — added override of
      the newer `shouldOverrideUrlLoading(WebView, WebResourceRequest)`
      overload (API 24+). The deprecated String-based overload only
      fires on API 21-23; on API 24+ only the WebResourceRequest
      overload is invoked. Without this override, http(s) links clicked
      on API 24+ devices would NOT be redirected to the system browser.
      The new overload delegates to the String overload for consistent
      behavior. Added imports for android.os.Build, android.webkit.
      WebResourceRequest (Build import retained for potential future
      SDK_INT checks).
    - No changes to other Java sources (MainActivity, StatsActivity,
      StockfishNative, ChessApp, EngineService, RootDetector,
      TlsSecurityHelper). All other Rev30 changes are in the JS layer
      (chess.src/ui.js — scroll restoration fix; chess.src/chess960.js
      — randomSPID modulo bias fix).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev31 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java (Rev31, GPL v3): UCI COMPLIANCE —
      startPonder() now has a 5-arg overload
      startPonder(fen, wtime, btime, winc, binc) that includes time
      params in the `go ponder` command. Per UCI spec, `go ponder` MUST
      include time params so the engine can switch to normal time
      management when `ponderhit` fires. The legacy single-arg
      startPonder(fen) is kept as @deprecated for backward compat
      (delegates to the 5-arg version with all zeros). For untimed
      games (all zeros), Java sends plain "go ponder" (no time params).
    - No changes to other Java sources (MainActivity, StatsActivity,
      ChessApp, ChessWebViewClient, EngineService, RootDetector,
      TlsSecurityHelper).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev32 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java (Rev32, GPL v3): UCI EVAL OPTIMIZATION per
      SF18 best-practices documentation:
      * engineEval() and engineEvalDeep() now call applyEvalModeOptions()
        BEFORE the eval search to set Contempt=0 (objective eval, default
        24 biases by avoiding draws), MultiPV=1 (max depth), UCI_ShowWDL=
        true (WDL output).
      * handleBestMove()'s STATE_EVAL case calls restoreGameplayOptions()
        to restore Contempt=24 (aggressive gameplay) and the user's
        MultiPV setting after the eval completes.
      * New private methods: applyEvalModeOptions(), restoreGameplayOptions().
    - No changes to other Java sources.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev33 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java (Rev33, GPL v3): SELDEPTH DISPLAY. New
      SELDEPTH_PATTERN regex. processInfoLine() parses seldepth.
      onEngineProgress gains 9th param (seldepth). onPonderProgress gains
      6th param (seldepth). onEngineEval gains 7th param (seldepth).
      MultiPV JSON includes seldepth field. New _lastEvalSeldepth field
      (reset alongside _lastEvalDepth).
    - No changes to other Java sources.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev34 changes:
    - No changes to Java sources. All Rev34 changes are in the JS layer
      (chess.src/chess960.js, stats.html).

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev35 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java (Rev35, GPL v3): TIMED-GAME ENGINE STOP FIX.
      New @JavascriptInterface methods:
      * engineStop(): hard-stop any engine state (STATE_GO/HINT/EVAL/
        PONDER). Sets _discardingPonderBestmove=true so the bestmove is
        silently consumed and dropped. Used by JS when clock expires or
        user resigns.
      * sendToEngine(String command): raw UCI command sender (fallback).
      engineGoTimed() now records the JS-call timestamp and deducts the
      setup overhead (stopAndWait + ucinewgame + readyok wait, up to 6s)
      from wtime/btime before sending "go". Also adds a safety margin
      (engineMoveOverhead, min 50ms). This prevents the engine from
      over-allocating search time based on stale clock values.
    - No changes to other Java sources.

  v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev36 changes:
    - StockfishNative.java (Rev36, GPL v3): engineStop() no longer sets
      _discardingPonderBestmove when engine is idle (STATE_NONE). Only
      sets the flag + sends "stop" when stateBefore != STATE_NONE.
      Prevents the next game's first bestmove from being silently
      discarded after an idle engineStop() call.
    - No changes to other Java sources.

