v1.1.0 Phase 58 (2026.7.5):
  - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): Two P0 concurrency fixes.
    (1) stopLatch TOCTOU race fix — the bestmove handler in readEngineOutput()
    now atomically captures-and-clears _stopLatch under _stopLatchLock (was:
    read volatile _stopLatch without holding the lock, creating a race with
    stopAndWaitForBestmove's timeout path that could incorrectly arm the
    _discardingPonderBestmove flag and discard the NEXT legitimate bestmove).
    The timeout path now only arms the discard flag if it still owns the latch
    (_stopLatch == stopLatch under the lock).
    (2) Heartbeat deadlock fix — the heartbeat thread's engineWriter.write("quit")
    call (zombie-detection branch) was synchronized on StockfishNative.this
    (same monitor as startHeartbeat), creating a deadlock risk: shutdown's
    _heartbeatThread.join(1000) would wait for the heartbeat to release `this`
    while the heartbeat was blocked on I/O. Now uses a dedicated _writerLock
    (new private final Object field) decoupled from the `this` monitor.
  - Other Java files: No changes.

v1.1.0 Phase 57+ (2026.7.5):
  - StockfishNative.java (GPL v3, DroidFish-derived): postJsCallback now checks
    `activity.isFinishing() || activity.isDestroyed()` before invoking
    `webView.evaluateJavascript(...)`. On some OEM ROMs (notably HyperOS 3),
    calling evaluateJavascript on a destroyed WebView's main thread throws
    IllegalStateException, which previously crashed the process during engine-
    init retries after the user exited the app. The guard logs and skips the
    callback instead.
  - EngineService.java (AGPL v3, original): Foreground-service wake lock
    acquisition changed from unbounded `wakeLock.acquire()` to bounded
    `wakeLock.acquire(30L * 60L * 1000L)` (30-minute timeout). If the OEM
    silently kills the service and onDestroy never runs, the wake lock is
    released automatically instead of holding the CPU awake indefinitely.

v1.1.0 Phase 57 (2026.7.4):
  - All Java files: No changes. Phase 57 fixes are in the JavaScript layer (ui.js)
    only — pure DOM/layout and visual-annotation cache fixes.

v1.1.0 Phase 56 (2026.7.4):
  - StockfishNative.java: Moved setGameDifficulty() call to BEFORE position fen in
    both engineGoTimed() and engineGoInternal(). Previously setGameDifficulty was
    called BETWEEN position fen and go — UCI commands are processed in order so this
    worked, but the UCI spec recommends setoption commands precede position/go. This
    refinement ensures all setoption commands (UCI_Chess960, UCI_LimitStrength,
    UCI_Elo, Skill Level) are sent before position fen, cleaner ordering. Verified
    Chess960+TimeControl UCI sequence: setoption UCI_Chess960 (with isready) →
    ucinewgame → isready → setoption difficulty → position fen (Shredder) →
    go wtime/btime/winc/binc.

v1.1.0 Phase 55 (2026.7.4):
  - No changes to Java source files in this phase. Phase 55 fixes a Chess960
    castling bug in stats.html (JavaScript) and game-logic.js (JavaScript).
    The Java-side StatsActivity just loads stats.html in a WebView; the fix is
    entirely within the JavaScript layer.

